 Rationalize the denominator of: $\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}+\sqrt{8}+\sqrt{32}}$.
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}+\sqrt{8}+\sqrt{32}}
&= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}+\sqrt{2\cdot4}+\sqrt{2\cdot4\cdot4}} \\
&= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}+2\sqrt{2}+4\sqrt{2}} \\
&= \frac{\sqrt{2}}{8\sqrt{2}} \\
&= \frac{\sqrt{2}}{8}\cdot \frac{\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{2}} \\
&= \frac{\sqrt{4}}{8} \\
&= \frac{2}{8} \\
&= \boxed{\frac{1}{4}}
\end{align*}
